WEBVTT

00:00:01.170 --> 00:00:02.490
Hi everyone.

00:00:02.490 --> 00:00:04.500
Today, I'm excited to share more

00:00:04.500 --> 00:00:07.440
about App Store pricing capabilities.

00:00:07.440 --> 00:00:10.143
I'm Camille and I work on the App Store pricing team.

00:00:10.980 --> 00:00:13.350
In this session, we'll start with an overview

00:00:13.350 --> 00:00:15.903
of the pricing capabilities on the App Store.

00:00:16.980 --> 00:00:18.180
Then, we'll talk

00:00:18.180 --> 00:00:20.610
about how the App Store global pricing tools

00:00:20.610 --> 00:00:22.950
can help you effortlessly price your content

00:00:22.950 --> 00:00:25.113
in 175 storefronts.

00:00:26.190 --> 00:00:29.220
Next, we'll explore the advanced tools available

00:00:29.220 --> 00:00:31.683
to customize pricing for each storefront.

00:00:32.670 --> 00:00:34.837
And finally, I'll share some examples

00:00:34.837 --> 00:00:36.960
of pricing configurations

00:00:36.960 --> 00:00:40.560
that can help you make the most out of these new features.

00:00:40.560 --> 00:00:41.673
So let's jump in.

00:00:43.530 --> 00:00:47.040
With a total of 175 different storefronts,

00:00:47.040 --> 00:00:49.830
the App Store makes it easy to distribute your apps

00:00:49.830 --> 00:00:51.663
and games across the world.

00:00:53.010 --> 00:00:54.837
In 72 of these storefronts,

00:00:54.837 --> 00:00:58.500
customers can make purchases in their local currency.

00:00:58.500 --> 00:01:01.800
For example, Japanese customers purchase in yen,

00:01:01.800 --> 00:01:04.350
Polish customers purchase in zloty,

00:01:04.350 --> 00:01:06.753
and Tanzanian customers purchase in shilling.

00:01:08.100 --> 00:01:12.030
Altogether, the App Store supports 44 local currencies,

00:01:12.030 --> 00:01:13.830
with the United States dollars

00:01:13.830 --> 00:01:16.623
and euro each supporting multiple storefronts.

00:01:18.300 --> 00:01:21.000
And in 77 of these storefronts,

00:01:21.000 --> 00:01:25.350
Apple collects and remits taxes on sales to customers.

00:01:25.350 --> 00:01:27.090
The scope changes every year,

00:01:27.090 --> 00:01:31.350
as new taxes are introduced or existing tax rates change.

00:01:31.350 --> 00:01:36.090
For example, 27 of these storefronts either introduced a tax

00:01:36.090 --> 00:01:39.003
or experienced a tax change in the last two years alone.

00:01:40.890 --> 00:01:43.650
Prices advertised to customers in all countries

00:01:43.650 --> 00:01:46.770
except the U.S. and Canada include taxes,

00:01:46.770 --> 00:01:49.230
so changes in tax may affect your earnings

00:01:49.230 --> 00:01:52.623
from App Store sales if prices aren't adjusted accordingly.

00:01:54.720 --> 00:01:57.210
To help you stay on top of changes in tax laws

00:01:57.210 --> 00:01:59.520
and fluctuations in exchange rate,

00:01:59.520 --> 00:02:02.460
Apple has developed a set of global pricing tools

00:02:02.460 --> 00:02:04.860
that makes it simple for you to price your apps

00:02:04.860 --> 00:02:07.413
and in-app purchases in all storefronts.

00:02:09.420 --> 00:02:13.050
Apple also provides a set of tools to let you manage pricing

00:02:13.050 --> 00:02:15.570
and availability by storefront.

00:02:15.570 --> 00:02:17.070
Let's walk through these tools,

00:02:17.070 --> 00:02:20.013
starting with a deep dive on the global pricing tools.

00:02:21.900 --> 00:02:24.000
With Apple's global pricing tools,

00:02:24.000 --> 00:02:26.910
you can select a base storefront for each app

00:02:26.910 --> 00:02:30.030
or in-app purchase you offer on the App Store.

00:02:30.030 --> 00:02:32.940
This allows you to select a storefront you're familiar with

00:02:32.940 --> 00:02:34.833
as the basis for global pricing.

00:02:35.730 --> 00:02:38.190
You'll be able to choose a price for this storefront

00:02:38.190 --> 00:02:40.825
among 900 price point options.

00:02:40.825 --> 00:02:44.219
Apple will then automatically generate comparable prices

00:02:44.219 --> 00:02:46.320
across the other storefronts,

00:02:46.320 --> 00:02:48.450
taking into account foreign exchange rates

00:02:48.450 --> 00:02:49.683
and certain taxes.

00:02:51.210 --> 00:02:53.250
These globally equalized prices follow

00:02:53.250 --> 00:02:56.220
the most common pricing conventions in each storefront,

00:02:56.220 --> 00:02:58.410
so customers see prices that's most relevant

00:02:58.410 --> 00:03:00.153
to their region and currency.

00:03:02.010 --> 00:03:04.440
Finally, prices other than your base

00:03:04.440 --> 00:03:06.180
will be automatically updated

00:03:06.180 --> 00:03:08.550
for foreign exchange and tax rate changes

00:03:08.550 --> 00:03:11.370
to help ensure your global prices stay comparable

00:03:11.370 --> 00:03:12.933
to your selected base price.

00:03:14.340 --> 00:03:16.920
So let's explore how global equalization works

00:03:16.920 --> 00:03:18.003
through an example.

00:03:19.260 --> 00:03:22.170
Suppose you select Germany as your base storefront

00:03:22.170 --> 00:03:25.980
and set a base price point of 7.99 euros.

00:03:25.980 --> 00:03:27.360
Based on this choice,

00:03:27.360 --> 00:03:29.220
Apple establishes similar prices

00:03:29.220 --> 00:03:31.980
in the remaining 174 storefronts

00:03:31.980 --> 00:03:34.023
based on local pricing conventions.

00:03:34.920 --> 00:03:36.540
For instance, the US,

00:03:36.540 --> 00:03:41.490
the UK and Canada follow a pricing convention ending in .99,

00:03:41.490 --> 00:03:44.430
while China has price points ending in 8.

00:03:44.430 --> 00:03:47.226
In Japan, we see even, rounded price points,

00:03:47.226 --> 00:03:51.330
and in Korea, we see a price like 9,901

00:03:51.330 --> 00:03:53.220
that starts with a repeating digit,

00:03:53.220 --> 00:03:56.339
a convention that is commonly used in Korea.

00:03:56.339 --> 00:03:59.550
Prices are globally equalized before tax,

00:03:59.550 --> 00:04:02.550
which means customers in each country pay approximately

00:04:02.550 --> 00:04:04.380
the same amount as your base price,

00:04:04.380 --> 00:04:06.483
but with local taxes added on top.

00:04:07.500 --> 00:04:09.739
As a result, proceeds in each storefront

00:04:09.739 --> 00:04:12.426
are approximately equalized.

00:04:12.426 --> 00:04:15.480
In this example, we can see that global proceeds

00:04:15.480 --> 00:04:16.860
are closely equalized

00:04:16.860 --> 00:04:19.713
to our proceeds of 4.70 euros in Germany,

00:04:20.880 --> 00:04:24.390
and they range from 4.45 euros in Japan

00:04:24.390 --> 00:04:26.523
to 4.88 euros in Canada.

00:04:28.530 --> 00:04:30.930
Additionally, the pricing of your apps

00:04:30.930 --> 00:04:34.080
and one-time in-app purchases will adjust automatically

00:04:34.080 --> 00:04:36.930
to maintain global prices aligned with your base price

00:04:36.930 --> 00:04:39.303
as foreign exchange and tax rates fluctuate.

00:04:42.180 --> 00:04:44.400
Thanks to these global pricing tools,

00:04:44.400 --> 00:04:47.250
you have an easy way to generate comparable prices

00:04:47.250 --> 00:04:49.110
for customers around the world,

00:04:49.110 --> 00:04:51.243
regardless of where they purchase from.

00:04:52.350 --> 00:04:55.380
The automated price updates help you effortlessly stay

00:04:55.380 --> 00:04:58.050
on top of foreign exchange and tax rate changes

00:04:58.050 --> 00:05:00.000
so that global prices stay equalized

00:05:00.000 --> 00:05:01.950
to the base price you have defined

00:05:01.950 --> 00:05:03.480
while making sure that customers

00:05:03.480 --> 00:05:06.107
in each storefront see recognizable prices

00:05:06.107 --> 00:05:08.133
that are relevant to their market.

00:05:09.000 --> 00:05:10.380
The global pricing tools

00:05:10.380 --> 00:05:12.900
also help your global earnings stay consistent

00:05:12.900 --> 00:05:15.808
and reduces your foreign exchange exposure.

00:05:15.808 --> 00:05:18.990
Finally, it also limits opportunities

00:05:18.990 --> 00:05:22.293
for customers to seek lower prices on certain storefronts.

00:05:23.280 --> 00:05:25.590
As we'll see in the second part of this presentation,

00:05:25.590 --> 00:05:28.770
you will always have the option to manually manage prices

00:05:28.770 --> 00:05:30.900
in any storefront if you prefer.

00:05:30.900 --> 00:05:33.300
However, if you select your own prices,

00:05:33.300 --> 00:05:35.610
you will not benefit from the automatic repricing

00:05:35.610 --> 00:05:37.017
for foreign exchange and tax,

00:05:37.017 --> 00:05:38.196
and you will be responsible

00:05:38.196 --> 00:05:41.013
for reflecting those changes in your prices.

00:05:43.290 --> 00:05:46.620
So how to make the most of the global equalization feature?

00:05:46.620 --> 00:05:49.593
The first step is to carefully select your base storefront.

00:05:50.430 --> 00:05:52.707
Apple will use the price you define in this storefront

00:05:52.707 --> 00:05:55.607
as the basis for generating comparable prices

00:05:55.607 --> 00:05:59.763
in the other 174 storefronts and 43 currencies.

00:06:00.660 --> 00:06:04.533
Your base storefront can be any of the 175 storefronts,

00:06:05.370 --> 00:06:07.050
and the price in your base storefront

00:06:07.050 --> 00:06:08.913
will never be automatically updated.

00:06:11.100 --> 00:06:12.780
Prices in the other storefronts,

00:06:12.780 --> 00:06:15.736
however, may be updated for foreign exchange and tax

00:06:15.736 --> 00:06:18.150
to maintain global prices equalized

00:06:18.150 --> 00:06:21.030
with the price you set for your base storefront.

00:06:21.030 --> 00:06:22.890
Please note that this does not apply

00:06:22.890 --> 00:06:24.843
to auto-renewable subscriptions.

00:06:26.430 --> 00:06:29.910
So how do you decide what your base storefront should be?

00:06:29.910 --> 00:06:31.710
If you cater to a single market,

00:06:31.710 --> 00:06:33.870
it may make sense to select that market

00:06:33.870 --> 00:06:35.070
as your base storefront.

00:06:36.060 --> 00:06:38.059
If you don't have a single focus market,

00:06:38.059 --> 00:06:40.980
you might consider your user base location

00:06:40.980 --> 00:06:43.290
to help determine a base storefront.

00:06:43.290 --> 00:06:46.500
For example, if most of your customer base is in Europe,

00:06:46.500 --> 00:06:47.333
it might make sense

00:06:47.333 --> 00:06:49.683
for you to choose a European country as base.

00:06:51.570 --> 00:06:53.910
Another consideration could be the currency

00:06:53.910 --> 00:06:55.950
in which your earnings are paid.

00:06:55.950 --> 00:06:57.000
It might make sense for you

00:06:57.000 --> 00:06:59.760
to align your base storefront and your earnings currency

00:06:59.760 --> 00:07:02.160
in order to keep things consistent.

00:07:02.160 --> 00:07:04.290
Note that it's not at all a requirement.

00:07:04.290 --> 00:07:06.930
For example, if you have selected your App Store earnings

00:07:06.930 --> 00:07:08.518
to be paid in Canadian dollars,

00:07:08.518 --> 00:07:11.640
but you select the U.S. as your base storefront,

00:07:11.640 --> 00:07:13.953
you will still be paid in Canadian dollars.

00:07:15.900 --> 00:07:18.900
Another consideration is currency volatility.

00:07:18.900 --> 00:07:21.600
If you choose a base storefront with a volatile currency,

00:07:21.600 --> 00:07:24.309
it may result in more frequent price adjustments compared

00:07:24.309 --> 00:07:26.043
with other storefronts.

00:07:27.000 --> 00:07:29.730
In any case, you will define a base storefront

00:07:29.730 --> 00:07:31.800
for each individual purchase.

00:07:31.800 --> 00:07:33.270
So depending on your business,

00:07:33.270 --> 00:07:35.280
you could choose different base storefronts

00:07:35.280 --> 00:07:37.595
for different in-app purchases.

00:07:37.595 --> 00:07:38.820
For in-app purchases

00:07:38.820 --> 00:07:41.280
without a base storefront explicitly defined,

00:07:41.280 --> 00:07:43.530
the base storefront defined at the app level

00:07:43.530 --> 00:07:47.050
is inherited by the associated in-app purchases.

00:07:47.050 --> 00:07:48.690
And if no base storefront

00:07:48.690 --> 00:07:51.630
is defined neither at the app or in-app level,

00:07:51.630 --> 00:07:54.213
the U.S. is the assumed base storefront by default.

00:07:56.010 --> 00:07:57.180
To illustrate the impact

00:07:57.180 --> 00:08:00.240
of your choice of base storefront on global prices,

00:08:00.240 --> 00:08:01.773
let's look at two scenarios.

00:08:03.030 --> 00:08:03.995
In the first scenario,

00:08:03.995 --> 00:08:06.660
Germany is selected as the base storefront

00:08:06.660 --> 00:08:09.840
with a base price of 7.99 euros.

00:08:09.840 --> 00:08:12.360
Comparable prices are automatically generated

00:08:12.360 --> 00:08:13.770
for the other storefronts,

00:08:13.770 --> 00:08:16.800
and prices will remain equalized with the German price,

00:08:16.800 --> 00:08:18.330
even if there are fluctuations

00:08:18.330 --> 00:08:20.253
in tax or foreign exchange rates.

00:08:21.090 --> 00:08:23.130
For instance, if the U.S. dollar

00:08:23.130 --> 00:08:25.380
and British pound weaken against the euro

00:08:25.380 --> 00:08:26.821
and other currencies,

00:08:26.821 --> 00:08:29.723
prices in the U.S. and the UK would increase

00:08:29.723 --> 00:08:32.523
to maintain price equalization with Germany.

00:08:34.050 --> 00:08:35.760
Now looking at the same scenario,

00:08:35.760 --> 00:08:37.800
this time with the United Kingdom selected

00:08:37.800 --> 00:08:39.600
as the base storefront.

00:08:39.600 --> 00:08:41.340
The starting point is the same,

00:08:41.340 --> 00:08:43.775
with a base price of 6.99 pounds

00:08:43.775 --> 00:08:46.620
and comparable prices automatically generated

00:08:46.620 --> 00:08:49.500
for the other storefronts, including Germany.

00:08:49.500 --> 00:08:52.231
However, if we consider the same change in foreign exchange

00:08:52.231 --> 00:08:53.965
as in our previous example,

00:08:53.965 --> 00:08:57.047
prices in the U.S. would remain the same while prices

00:08:57.047 --> 00:09:00.240
in the other storefronts would this time decrease

00:09:00.240 --> 00:09:01.683
to reflect the same change.

00:09:03.060 --> 00:09:05.160
Once you have chosen a base storefront,

00:09:05.160 --> 00:09:07.533
the second step is to choose your base price.

00:09:08.430 --> 00:09:10.440
You can choose from 900 price points

00:09:10.440 --> 00:09:13.050
in the currency of your base storefront.

00:09:13.050 --> 00:09:17.070
By default, you have access to 800 prices up to $1,000

00:09:17.070 --> 00:09:19.380
and similar prices worldwide.

00:09:19.380 --> 00:09:21.390
On request, you can also access

00:09:21.390 --> 00:09:25.713
an additional 100 higher price points as high as $10,000.

00:09:26.550 --> 00:09:29.280
Prices start at 29 cents in the US,

00:09:29.280 --> 00:09:31.260
with lower priced options available

00:09:31.260 --> 00:09:33.120
in most emerging markets.

00:09:33.120 --> 00:09:36.240
For example, the lowest price in India is 9 rupee,

00:09:36.240 --> 00:09:38.337
which is about 9 U.S. dollar cents,

00:09:38.337 --> 00:09:41.273
and the lowest price in China is 1 Chinese yuan,

00:09:41.273 --> 00:09:44.073
which is equivalent to 15 U.S. dollar cents.

00:09:45.900 --> 00:09:47.580
For all markets, you will be able

00:09:47.580 --> 00:09:50.490
to choose among several common pricing conventions

00:09:50.490 --> 00:09:52.530
and select the one that is the most suited

00:09:52.530 --> 00:09:54.123
to your marketing purposes.

00:09:56.610 --> 00:09:59.395
Looking, for example, at the U.S. 900 prices,

00:09:59.395 --> 00:10:02.010
we can see that steps between price points

00:10:02.010 --> 00:10:03.960
are smaller for lower price points

00:10:03.960 --> 00:10:07.440
and gradually decrease as prices increase.

00:10:07.440 --> 00:10:09.270
10 cents price steps are supported

00:10:09.270 --> 00:10:14.270
until $10 and 50 cents price steps are supported until $50.

00:10:15.480 --> 00:10:16.920
In terms of conventions,

00:10:16.920 --> 00:10:19.530
you have the choice between four conventions.

00:10:19.530 --> 00:10:23.910
You can opt to use .99 endings, like 9.99,

00:10:23.910 --> 00:10:26.010
or to incorporate different price endings,

00:10:26.010 --> 00:10:29.783
like whole numbers or endings in .90 or .95

00:10:29.783 --> 00:10:31.020
that could be useful

00:10:31.020 --> 00:10:33.573
for annual plans or discounts, for example.

00:10:35.070 --> 00:10:36.540
Looking at another example,

00:10:36.540 --> 00:10:39.150
with the 900 price points available for China,

00:10:39.150 --> 00:10:42.690
we see that smallest price steps start this time at 0.5 yuan

00:10:42.690 --> 00:10:44.610
and are supported until 10 yuan,

00:10:44.610 --> 00:10:48.353
then move to steps of 1 yuan, supported until 200 yuans.

00:10:49.640 --> 00:10:52.800
You also have the choice between five conventions.

00:10:52.800 --> 00:10:54.210
For lower price points,

00:10:54.210 --> 00:10:58.449
you can choose whole numbers or endings in .80 or .90.

00:10:58.449 --> 00:11:02.280
For higher price points, you could opt for endings in 9,

00:11:02.280 --> 00:11:05.823
like 99, or endings in 8, like 98.

00:11:08.820 --> 00:11:12.360
You can request access to the 100 price points above $1,000

00:11:12.360 --> 00:11:15.360
by filling out a request form on the developer website

00:11:15.360 --> 00:11:16.983
at the address shown on screen.

00:11:19.124 --> 00:11:22.860
Once you have chosen a base storefront and a base price,

00:11:22.860 --> 00:11:25.590
Apple's automated global pricing features provide you

00:11:25.590 --> 00:11:27.540
with a great way to effortlessly price

00:11:27.540 --> 00:11:29.043
your content worldwide.

00:11:30.540 --> 00:11:33.000
As we've seen in our Germany example,

00:11:33.000 --> 00:11:36.180
Apple automatically calculates worldwide prices equalized

00:11:36.180 --> 00:11:38.820
to your base price before tax,

00:11:38.820 --> 00:11:40.799
following common pricing conventions,

00:11:40.799 --> 00:11:43.320
so that customers see great prices

00:11:43.320 --> 00:11:45.537
regardless of their region.

00:11:45.537 --> 00:11:49.350
Additionally, if you choose automated global pricing,

00:11:49.350 --> 00:11:52.230
prices for your apps and one-time in-app purchases

00:11:52.230 --> 00:11:53.910
will automatically be updated

00:11:53.910 --> 00:11:57.510
to keep you on top of foreign exchange and tax rate changes.

00:11:57.510 --> 00:12:01.184
Reprices happen only when specific criteria are met.

00:12:01.184 --> 00:12:04.530
Typically, pricing for a storefront will be updated

00:12:04.530 --> 00:12:08.265
if its currency strengthens or weakens by at least 10%,

00:12:08.265 --> 00:12:11.313
and the change is sustained over a couple of quarters.

00:12:12.150 --> 00:12:14.760
This keeps global pricing equalized over time,

00:12:14.760 --> 00:12:16.650
but it also keeps prices stable

00:12:16.650 --> 00:12:19.743
when foreign exchange rate changes are only short-lived.

00:12:20.940 --> 00:12:22.980
Larger foreign exchange rate changes,

00:12:22.980 --> 00:12:26.730
like 25% or more, may trigger faster action.

00:12:26.730 --> 00:12:29.970
Apple uses publicly available exchange rate information

00:12:29.970 --> 00:12:31.890
from financial data providers

00:12:31.890 --> 00:12:34.443
to evaluate these changes in foreign exchange.

00:12:35.370 --> 00:12:37.020
Prices may also be updated

00:12:37.020 --> 00:12:41.220
whenever a country introduces a new tax or a tax change.

00:12:41.220 --> 00:12:42.390
It's important to note

00:12:42.390 --> 00:12:44.520
that auto-renewable subscription prices

00:12:44.520 --> 00:12:46.200
are not automatically adjusted

00:12:46.200 --> 00:12:49.050
to account for foreign exchange and tax changes,

00:12:49.050 --> 00:12:50.880
but you can update your subscription pricing

00:12:50.880 --> 00:12:52.773
at any time in App Store Connect.

00:12:54.390 --> 00:12:56.280
Any price change will be notified

00:12:56.280 --> 00:12:58.452
by email at least 14 days in advance,

00:12:58.452 --> 00:13:01.200
and the new prices will be displayed in App Store Connect

00:13:01.200 --> 00:13:03.453
for your review from the time of notice.

00:13:06.210 --> 00:13:08.265
When an automatic price change is scheduled,

00:13:08.265 --> 00:13:11.520
you'll see it appear in the Upcoming Changes section

00:13:11.520 --> 00:13:14.220
of your price schedule on App Store Connect.

00:13:14.220 --> 00:13:17.324
New prices will be posted at least 14 days in advance

00:13:17.324 --> 00:13:18.870
to give you the opportunity

00:13:18.870 --> 00:13:22.230
to review the changes to the impacted storefronts.

00:13:22.230 --> 00:13:25.410
We'll explore where and how to review the upcoming changes

00:13:25.410 --> 00:13:26.913
in App Store Connect shortly.

00:13:28.350 --> 00:13:30.810
For apps and one-time in-app purchases

00:13:30.810 --> 00:13:32.430
that were created before the launch

00:13:32.430 --> 00:13:35.100
of these new features in March 2023

00:13:35.100 --> 00:13:37.380
and that do not have a base storefront,

00:13:37.380 --> 00:13:39.270
you may also take this opportunity

00:13:39.270 --> 00:13:40.800
to edit your base storefront

00:13:40.800 --> 00:13:43.350
if you'd like the reprice to be based on your price

